Protesters close off a street in Richards Bay on 21 August 2019 JOHANNESBURG - Angry residents in Richards Bay in KwaZulu-Natal have brought the CBD to a standstill. They've blockaded a road leading into the town with trucks and burning tyres. READ: Family ambushed in deadly KZN home invasion Tensions first began a few weeks ago, when residents and taxi operators assaulted whoonga users, accusing them of petty crimes. Since then, trucks drivers have joined the protests, complaining about the employment of foreigners. Some are accusing the foreigners of peddling drugs in the area. Trucks blockade roads in Richards Bay on 21 August 2019